author: cbs8
title: Interstate 22 signs to be unveiled in northern Mississippi
text:
NEW ALBANY, Miss. (AP) - New signs being unveiled this week will give U.S. Highway 78 across northern Mississippi a second name - Interstate 22.
A ceremony to show off the I-22 signs is scheduled for Friday in New Albany.
The Commercial Appeal reports ( http://bit.ly/1KgHoiK ) the four-lane highway covers roughly 200 miles between Memphis, Tennessee, and Birmingham, Alabama.
It is part of the emerging I-269 hub that's under construction as a 30-mile loop around Memphis.
U.S. 78 was designated as a future interstate corridor. The Mississippi Department of Transportation's application to change it to I-22 has been sent to the U.S. Department of Transportation and the Federal Highway Administration for final approval.
